.TH "drm_bridge_chain_mode_valid" 9 "drm_bridge_chain_mode_valid" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_bridge_chain_mode_valid \- validate the mode against all bridges in the encoder chain.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "enum drm_mode_status" drm_bridge_chain_mode_valid
.BI "(struct drm_bridge *bridge "  ","
.BI "const struct drm_display_info *info "  ","
.BI "const struct drm_display_mode *mode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bridge" 12
bridge control structure
.IP "info" 12
display info against which the mode shall be validated
.IP "mode" 12
desired mode to be validated
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Calls \fIdrm_bridge_funcs.mode_valid\fP for all the bridges in the encoder
chain, starting from the first bridge to the last. If at least one bridge
does not accept the mode the function returns the error code.
.SH "NOTE"
the bridge passed should be the one closest to the encoder.
.SH "RETURN"
MODE_OK on success, drm_mode_status Enum error code on failure
